caption: Visited again after 3-4 years. Just nice restaurant worth any visit.  My favorites are the shrimp, scallop and mochi dessert with Macaron. All of the dishes are great! I really admire the idea to cook head and tail of one shrimp in two ways. Fantastic!!!  Time between dishes are just short/long enough. Waiters are gentle and polite. Price is great for a Japanese fine dining.  I wish the restaurant and owner could always have great business. Hope the whole restaurant can last for many many years.  Why not? Of course!
The sushi, sashimi and nigiri were excellent. Like so  good it defies explanation, like why or how is it this good. The service was great too. Will definitely be back.
Amazing, melt-in-your mouth sushi!
Our go-to place for Sashimi and other fine Japanese dishes in the area. Never disappointed.
Excellent food and great service. Don't miss the scallop and the lobster maki

The chef’s choice sashimi platter was beautiful even when enjoyed in the comfort of home! Fresh fish, the creamiest scallops and all topped with salmon roe (bonus yum). Rolls were good, but this was the star. We’ll definitely return for delivery and hopefully in person for Omakase someday.

This is extremely high-quality sushi for a "neighborhood" place. Hamachi always has a wonderful soft texture and briny flavor, and the negi-hamachi rolls w/ white pepper are genius. Escolar and sake are also top-notch. I look forward to when in-house dining is available to have their omakase again -- but until then, you won't find better quality nigiri (or maki) on the northside. Support them w/ takeout!

Holy cow, they give a lot of food. Ordered a katsu donburi, and it came with a huge bowl of rice, a decent amount of katsu, topped with a bowl of udon. Didn't expect the udon, ended up super stuffed. The only downside was that there was about a 15 min wait at 2:40pm on a Saturday.
"Love the food, but this location always seems to have slow service."
Great service, food taste average.The staffs are good too.
Very good quality seafood. Chef's palette is slightly on the sweet side, but I really like it. Great pairing of saki and whiskeys
Good place to hang and eat some good food. The bill was appropriate for the quality.
Great food with quality ingredients.  The service was very helpful and welcoming. Prices are appropriate. I can see why they have so many great reviews.
It was so tasty. The staff was friendly and observant. The place has a good feel to it.
Great place to relax, people watch, eat good food or all the above.  It has a great atmosphere.
Tried this spot once with my friend and I am obsessed ever since. I love the excellent vibes and delicious dishes and drinks. Kudos.
Incredible food!
Very good food, great service,  overall nice dinner date experience.
Excellent sushi
One of my preferred spots for quality japanese food. reminds me of a place in new york i loved to visit.
A preferred spot for Japanese food. Arrived at five, it wasn't busy. The service was friendly and sociable.
Had a very good experience in this spot with my kids. The food was served quick and the customer service is just awesome. Prices are reasonable.
Had a great time at Raisu Japanese Fine Dining. Waitress was very kind and timely with our orders. The head chef also took time to talk with us and gifted a free appetizer! Highly recommend.
They offer an awesome range of fresh food. I liked dining here. Staff members are always helpful, rates are affordable and the place is always well organised.
Delicious sushi. Amazing presentation. Great service.

Really loved this Irving Park gem! The space is smallish, and almost every guest has a good view of the sushi counter where the chef and his assistants perform their magic. Interesting selection of Japanese beers +in addition to sake and wine). We opted for the Omakase menu, which includes some warm items but is primarily sushi- and sashimi-based. Which is totally fine with me! The selections were "traditional with a twist": everything was recognizable, but most items included a small unique tweak that kept things interesting. Overall, highly recommended!
I saw a review of them on Check Please on Friday 2/7 and came on the Sunday 2/9. The entire dining experience was excellent,and I ran into the person who recommended the restaurant on Check Please.
I always stop purchasing some food in this place. I love the speedy customer service and well made food. Great work.
Very good 👍
Amazing experience!
This spot knows how to treat their clients. Always with a kind approach. The food is fairly priced, constantly delicious and clean.

Really good.  Complex style in an Irving Park sushi restaurant.  The sushi was up there with the best in Chicago.  I liked the Omakase and way they are uplifting every piece.  Reminds me of NYC.  They also offer simpler sushi and prices are good.
Intimate place.  Sit at the sushi bar.

Raisu has such delicious and fresh sushi! I came here with my husband and we got the omakase 101! I highly recommend this if you’ve never done a traditional omakase before. It is all so fresh and so affordable!
Good Sushi, nice place and one heck of an owner.  NICELY DONE!!
Excellent service. Sushi was very good. Some of the flavor combinations were a little odd.  Overall worth a try!
Great events,  really attentive staff.  Clean and not super pricey. The food was amazing.  I bought the 5 course package for my mom and I and we had a wonderful time.

Beware, beware, buyer beware- Raisu has the appearance of a neighborhood restaurant.  And even the reviews and the $$$ did not warn us.  The food was marvelous, the drinks interesting and we did the Japanese “Omakase” where we let the chef pick our sushi- for a party of 4 the bill was $746.!  No one warned us.  Our waiter was slick, oh so informative about everything we ate except for the price.  We don’t live in a neighborhood that charges a Mortage payment for a dinner for 4.   I will never go back and I will warn anyone who asks.  Just shameful and evil.  We wanted this to be our neighborhood restaurant.  Never again.
Amazing place.  Frankly one of the best meals I've ever had in Chicago.

Overpriced for the portion size , the inferno roll and scallop roll was really good I spent over 100$ between 2 appetizers , 4 rolls and 1 drink. Me and my girl still left hungry, the service was fantastic but for that price not worth it. I've had way better sushi for less.
Best sushi and sashimi I've *ever* had - not just in Chicago.  Insane flavor combinations, fish flown in fresh from Japan.  Fantastic, creative, you won't regret coming here!
Excellent but very expensive
Try the inferno Dragon. You will not regret it
Most excellent sushi! :) :) :)

I like Raisu.  I like it because it is 2 blocks from my house. And if I feel like some simple ok sushi I walk over.  According to google it is one of the best Sushi joints in Chicago.  It is not.  It's a mediocre run of the mill sushi spot it is not Japanese fine dining lol. The fish is just ok.  I have had a few pieces that were kinda suspect. The staff are super nice but dont ask them to make anything special that is not on the menu
Ordered pickup empanadas. They are so tasty!!! The crust is so flaky and the insides were all really great.

Really exceptional quality fish for the price, some of the best cuts of fish I've found in chicago. I went through and read a lot of the negative reviews and, generally and unfortunately, those people dont understand how to properly eat or judge sushi. Solid spot imo.
Loved everything about our omakase experience. I definitely recommend you try their omakase!

I have never wrote a review before for a restaurant but I am for Raisu.  My boyfriend and I did the 'Omakase' option which is letting the chef choose all your courses for you.  I can't begin to tell you how special it was.  Everything came out looking great and tasting even better. Our waiter was so friendly and treated us like we were his only table even though he had many.   I couldn't recommend this place more.  I also recommend sitting at the bar so you can watch the chef prepare everything!
Excellent menu options, incredible daily specials, knowledgeable wait staff.
Wow! All seafood were fresh into perfection. It was a special,promotional stuff. But it was great experienced . The fee was expensive but! It was all worth it..
(Translated by Google) Amaziiiiing  (Original) Amaziiiiing
Good food, good service. I made a reservation but probably didn't need one on a weeknight. It was surprisingly affordable
Over priced. Too small portion of meals. not worthy.
Food is amazing! Service is great! Their signature dishes were very creative and tasted incredible. Highly recommended.
I was there with my brother. We had a great time. The drinks and the sushi amazed me.
This is the best sushi place I ever been. The chefs are very nice and friendly. Staffs treated us like the king and queen. I would definitely recommend this place to others.
They just waste your time, very stupid service
The food here is very good.  Love it!  Will come back again.
Great place to eat. good food and nice people.
Great food and service

Litterally the worst $100 meal I’ve had ever. We had 2 rolls, 1 beer, a peligrino, tea, and hamachi appetizer.  Expensive, slow service and I’ve had better sushi from Jewel.  Let me be clear, if the bill was $20, I still would have been disappointed.  Interesting factoid, they must be going under because if you ask for Soy Sauce, they bring you one tiny dipping dish portion, not the bottle, which we desperately needed to cover the taste of the food. I can’t fogure out what they are spending the other $99 in profit on, but it’s not fresh fish.  Don’t waste your time or money on this place. The best thing we had was the Bottled beer.
Great sushi. Not too many other options but if you're specifically looking for sushi this is a great place to go.
We loved everything we ate here, but signature fish stole the show - seaweed salad with fried banana, fried calamari, giant chicken wings, various signature nigiri and signature maki
Great sushi. And it's not overpriced. The restaurant is beautiful too. With the trip.
Good sushi, but expensive. Miso was definitely too expensive for what it was
Good Food.
Absolutely the best sushi I've ever had. We ordered the omakase and it was amazing. Blue fin tuna melted in your mouth. Insanely good!!

I live really close, so was eager to try. They fly in the fish from japan every Wednesday and Friday. My friend and I came in on a Wednesday. The inferno dragon roll was AMAZING! We also tried the black widow and tornado, and those were also very delicious. I highly recommend their sashimi or nigiri because you can definitely taste the freshness of the fish.
Excellent sushi. Maria waited on us, she had excellent recommendations and gave us tastings of the sake.
Try the omakase. Chef Simon will surprise you with his inventive and tasty flavor profiles. The quality of the seafood is top-notch. The service staff is efficient and attentive.
Best sushi you're going to find on the Northwest side of the city
Super Fresh - great atmosphere, the wait staff has great knowledge of the menu.
Counter seats for a fantastic omakase meal from Simon are the way to go!  Phenomenal meal. Loved how his courses compared traditional with his signature style/taste.  Highly recommend it!

For the omakase on weekdays, it is ABSOLUTELY worth it. The quality and quantity for an omakase was worth it. We sat at the sushi bar and chit chatted with the chef while he prepared everything. It was fun to banter and see him prepare everything. A bit intimidating since he’s literally in your face watching your reaction to the food, but with the good food there wasn’t much to hide from him. Also, he had expensive rare aged Japanese whiskeys. He was considerate to sell us the less expensive sake because our palates would not be able to discern the difference. He said next time we come and if we had a few more sakes in our lives he would recommend his more rare stuff.

(Translated by Google) Very good Japanese restaurant. Refined, fresh and delicious dishes. Pleasant, sober and pleasant setting and service.  (Original) Très bon restaurant japonais. Plats raffinés, frais et délicieux. Cadre et service agréable, sobre et plaisant.
Great food and great service!  Nice ambiance too. :)
Love the place it's amazing . I give it 5 thumbs up !!!! Nicely done MR. JACK.

Raisu is one of the best sushi experiences in Chicago. Especially for the Irving Park / North Center area. The sushi is high quality because they care about the taste and age of the fish. When my husband and I ate at Raisu for the first time, we had scallops flown in straight from Hokkaido. You don't get more authentic than that!

This place is the real deal when it comes to sushi. The fish melts in your mouth just like it does in Japan. They even had a high end sake that I was only able to find in Tokyo. Great staff as well, truly a great experience
(Translated by Google) The best sushi rice I have ever eaten, the tuna sashimi is so delicious.  (Original) 吃过的最好吃的寿司米，金枪鱼生鱼片巨好吃。
Fantastic sushi, excellent service.  Price is right.

Everything we ordered was excellent.  We started with the the Scallop Special Sashimi, and it was some of the best scallops we've eaten.  Followed that with Salmon Nigiri (Delicious), and the incredible Lobster Special Maki pictured.  The Inferno Dragon Maki was also amazing. Service was great, and we'll definitely be back.
Portions are healthy and quality is great!

Fish is fresh.  Probably some of the best uni and scallop nigiri I've ever had.  However, the slices of fish on the nigiri are slightly on the thin side which threw off the fish-to-rice ratio for me.  I also found the rice, while tasty, not to hold together well.  Also the dressings they use on the nigiri fish are too much which detract from the flavor of the fresh fish they use.  It does give the fish a nice glistening look though.  I also found that the creative toppings on the signature nigiri didn't work for me except for the hamachi one with jalapeno.  Service is decent, staff is friendly, and atmosphere is nice (quite a bit of space inside).  Full bar, with the standard sushi beer options.  This is certainly a place to check out if you like nigiri.  I wouldn't hesitate to go back, especially if I am in the area.  However, my own personal preference is I still like Ora and Juno a little more.  Fish here is just as fresh as Kastu, Ora, and Juno.  So chances are if you like those other places you will like Raisu too.

I live in the neighborhood and I can honestly say this is the best restaurant that has been in that space. The food was delicious, when you walk in it smells like a great sushi place, not fishy like lower quality sushi restaurants. we ordered one of every maki roll and I had a hard time picking my favorite. try them all! there was a blue gill appetizer on special that I thought was only just okay but everything else was fantastic. recommend the inferno dragon maki roll
Extremely fresh sushi. Very friendly and prompt service.
Great quality shashimi in a nondescript location.
The sweet shrimp is highly recommend.
Amazing food, one of the best sushi restaurants in Chicago!

I love this place. The sushi quality is top notch and the staff is very friendly. The look and feel of Raisu is great. It's a very warm and friendly place. The price is pretty high but it is because the fish is fresh from Japan and you can easily tell it's legit.
Excellent.  Fish was fresh and overall great quality. Wish we had done less rolls and more sashimi and nigiri.
Superb dining, fish is so fresh. Dishes are beautiful. Twice in a week hope to be back very soon.
Tried their Omakase once again. There will be definitely a third visit.
Best sushi I have ever had
The food is mediocre, the price is expensive, the service is friendly. Would not visit again.
Place is expensive despite of $$ marking on the map,fancy interior and dinnerware but poor menu and food below average.
Overpriced mediocre sort of sushi .... very disappointing

This place opened in my neighborhood and I've been going since their soft-opening. I LOVE their fish! Very fresh, the sake is my favorite. Their soups are also really delicious. The service has always been attentive and friendly. Really nice decor inside and a nice spot for dinner. Highly recommend!
Very good elegant Japanese cuisine.

What a wonderful surprise! We've been meaning to try out this restaurant for a while, and finally had dinner there last night. This place offers the best sushi we have had in a long time. The atmosphere is classy, the service is friendly, and the food is just amazing! The presentation is outstanding- definitely order the inferno dragon, you will see what I'm referring to. Management and chef, keep it up! We will definitely come back and will bring friends along.

The Japanese fine dinning that located a little out of the city. But if you are a big fan of fresh sashimi and sushi , you need to come here. They have so many good menu to try. Make sure you try: DELUXE SEAFOOD BOWL, THE OCEANS OFFERINGS.
Excellent service and equally excellent food, totally recommended!
Great service. Excellent sushi offerings and rotating seasonal items let you know the fish is fresh. Best sushi I have had in Chicago in my 15 years here. A must try!

Take out a loan if you must and come feast on the very best sushi in Chicago. Emily our server is a wonderful guide to the menu and Jack the owner is very attentive to the guests needs. The scallop with torched miso is a game changer.
This place is fabulous. Freshest sushi I've had. Sweet potato and crab soup is also excellent. Good, friendly service.
Food is good to excellent. Wine list less so.
Great place for special nigiri flavor combinations.  Highly encourage all sushi enthusiasts to visit.

Expensive, but totally worth it. (Apparently they fly some of the fish in from Japan) Our waiter was friendly and knowledgeable, and made excellent recommendations. Their signature nigiri and sashimi runs far more experimental than traditional, which depending on your tastes is either a pro or a con. The traditional nigiri was amazing, and so were the rolls. If you have the cash, I would highly recommended going to Raisu.

One of the best sushi spots in Chicago. If Paula Dean opened a sushi place, this would be it. Everything was so buttery. Raisu is a great name, but I'm gonna call this place affectionately "Fish Butter." Stop in, eat this Sushi, tell me it's not fantastic.
Super decent place for Japanese Fine Dining. So addicted to bluefin tuna nigiri! The best place you can enjoy quality food with less money!!
Live just down the street from the place and absolutely LOVED IT. Service is amazing and hands down the best sushi I've had in the city.
Amazing. Preparation, fish quality, atmosphere... everything was perfect. Hands down the best sushi I've had in Chicago. Sit at the bar and talk with the chef, Simon. He'll take good care of you!
Really special. Simon is a mastercraftsman and the overall experience here is great. Nigiri with sublime toppings. Fresh and flair balanced well.
I've been to Raisu twice and it just keeps getting better.  This is the best sushi I've had in a while.  The signature nigiri are all highly, highly recommended.
Everything is so fresh and delicious!
Excellent  Very fresh and well executed sushi. Had a mini omakase for lunch and it was outstanding.  Sweet potato soup with crab Bluefin Tuna Salmon Sea Breem Shrimp Spanish Mackrel  I will be back

We loved the soups (house miso and sweet potato puree with crab). Both freshly made and tasty. Miso was not made from a just-add-water pouch like many other sushi restaurants in Chicago. We also had the samurai roll, which was delicious and the presentation was cool. Also had their fried calamari with salt-n-pepper; another tasty appetizer. We will be back for more!
Great sushi. Some unique twists. Wonderful service!
Incredible food and amazing service!
Outstanding! food, service and atmosphere
Excellent sushi and a great staff!
